@page "/"

<h3>Field-Level Async Validation — Blazor Web App</h3>
<p>
    This app demonstrates the <strong>new field-level async validation</strong> added to Blazor's
    <code>DataAnnotationsValidator</code> and <code>EditContext</code>. Unlike the existing
    form-level samples that manually call <code>Validator.TryValidateObjectAsync</code> on submit,
    these pages use <code>&lt;DataAnnotationsValidator /&gt;</code> which now <strong>automatically</strong>
    validates each field asynchronously when its value changes.
</p>

<div class="alert alert-primary">
    <strong>Key difference:</strong> Existing Blazor samples validate the entire model on submit
    (form-level). This app validates individual fields on change (field-level) using
    <code>Validator.TryValidatePropertyAsync</code> — powered by the new <code>EditContext</code>
    APIs: <code>AddValidationTask</code>, <code>IsValidationPending</code>, and
    <code>IsValidationFaulted</code>.
</div>

